The paper discusses the application of projective simulation (PS) to artificial intelligence (AI), which falls under the category of machine learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI. The paper also compares the performance of the PS agent with existing models, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.RO (robotics). The use of benchmarking problems such as the grid-world and mountain-car problem suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SY (systems and control) and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing).
